The war, was not in fact about Saddam himself. If Mass Murder, opression and other things was so important, America would at least not Deal with Saudi Arabia, Pakistan, China, and a long long list of other countries you are 'turning a blind eye on'.<br>
<br>
The fact of the matter is, that while Saddam being a Bastard was not the main reason the war was started.<br>
<br>
The glaring GLARING point you are metaphorically sweeping under the carpet, is weapons of mass destruction, this is pretty much the position that was touted for 6 months + leading up to the war.<br>
<br>
This is what the majority of people are actually pissed off about, seeing as you can't seem to do simple math, I'll point it out.<br>
<br>
A = The war was pushed because of WMD. If it wasn't, then 95 % of what the US Administration was bullshit (which is bad!)<br>
B = The pre-emptive war over WMD was not really justified. (North Korea, Iran, Lack of evidence which should have shown itself where the accusations justified are a demonstration of this)<br>
<br>
A + B = People think the war was unjustified.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now. I agree that Saddam should have been taken out, and in fact, Had the 2002 State of the Union Address Had these Words : <br>
<br>
&quot;We Cannot let the worlds worst men torture and kill their own people&quot;<br>
<br>
Rather than <br>
<br>
&quot;We Cannot let the worlds worst men in control of the worlds worst weapons&quot;<br>
<br>
I would have supported bush vehemently from the start.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now, you can continue to argue how justified the war is for taking out Saddam. I'd agree with you.<br>
<br>
But Make no mistake, had there been 0 evidence of WMD, and there was a wide consensus among the security services that Iraq had no WMD at all, this war would not have happened.<br>
<br>
And That, my simple minded friend, is why most people disagree.<br>
<br>
To complain at how Saddam is a bastard therefore the war was justified, is the same as drinking your own piss because of a fetish, then saying it's okay because you were thirsty.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
I'd agree with chudd on Keeping troops there though.<br>
<br>
Whatever damage was done, is done.<br>
<br>
The only thing left is the future, and that solely revolves around the Iraqi people, giving them the future and the lives that they deserve is priority number one, and making Iraq a prosperous and free country in the long term can only be a good thing. <p><br>
