<br>
Look, I'll spell it out.<br>
<br>
I disagree with the war because of what the US Administration has been peddling for the last 8 months, not that I disagree that Saddam should have been taken out. The two are seperate for any cogent human being.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
when have i turned a blind eye to them, saudia arabia is the next government we should take out. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Look. It's quite simple. I'm arguing on why the US government was not justified. If they were after human rights, they would not be turning a blind eye to Saudi and other places.<br>
<br>
Whether you did or not, is irrelevant. It prooves no point here. <br>
<br>
I am not disagreeing that Saddam needed to go, because I agree with that. What I am disagreeing with why the US went to war. Which are NOT the same thing.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>to me, i don't care what bush said, i don't care what justifications he said he had for starting the war. taking out saddam was a great thing. if bush had said we need to take out saddam because he's sending little green aliens to america to give everyone anal probes, i would have backed him. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I shall slowly attempt to peel back the viel of ignorance from your eyes.<br>
<br>
<br>
A = Saddam being a bastard was not the reason for this war (directly).<br>
<br>
B = We are disagreeing with the reasons for this war.<br>
<br>
C = You say we are idiots because Saddam being a bastard justifies the war.<br>
<br>
D = War is Fought for a Reason.<br>
<br>
<br>
Lets spell it out slowly.<br>
<br>
We<br>
Are<br>
Disagreeing<br>
Over<br>
The<br>
Reasons<br>
For<br>
War,<br>
Not<br>
That<br>
Saddam<br>
Is<br>
A<br>
Bad<br>
Guy<br>
They<br>
Are<br>
Two<br>
Seperate,<br>
Completley<br>
different<br>
Things.<br>
<br>
The Reasons for war are not the same things as the benefits of the war. <p><br>
