If we insist upon policing the world then should we not also be held to the same standards we demand of others?  How is it ok to declare war on Iraq for violations of the various UN mandates when we ourselves clearly went against the UN and our allies to do so?<br>
<br>
How has our invasion of Iraq curbed terrorism?  It looks like it has escalated to the point where you can count on at least 1 American dead each and every day due to an act of terrorism.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I am not disagreeing that Saddam needed to go, because I agree with that. What I am disagreeing with why the US went to war. Which are NOT the same thing.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I agree with this 100%.<br>
<br>
We need to do a few simple things<br>
<br>
1) keep our word<br>
<br>
2) treat our allies with respect<br>
<br>
3) obey the same rules we hold others to<br>
<br>
4) have a well thought out plan before we go to war so as not to leave our men in women in harms way any longer than necessary<br>
<br>
5) work with the rest of the world so as not to shoulder the burden of costs both physical and financial.<br>
<br>
6) be honest<br>
<br>
If we did those simple things we would already have UN support, troops and money from our various allies, and most likely an Iraqi populace that appreciated us being there rather than one that dances in celebration over a downed helicopter.<br>
<br>
I don't pretend to have all the answers, but what we are doing now is clearly not working as intended. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-family:verdana;font-size:xx-small;">Verminnarrd Kinslayer a Dark Elf Mage of no level currently worthy of note</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm26.showMessageRange?topicID=41.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm26.showMessageRange?topicID=41.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a> <b>3</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm26.showPrevMessage?topicID=41.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm26.showNextMessage?topicID=41.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=48><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm26.emailToFriend?topicID=41.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm26.threadControl?topicID=41.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm26.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=41.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  